<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>
<subsection xml:id="lec-situacionesDeSumaYResta" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">

<shorttitle>Lección 2 </shorttitle>
<title>Lección 2 -<nbsp/></title>
<title>Situaciones de suma y resta</title>


<!-- ============================================ 
  Objetivos de aprendizaje                        
=================================================  -->

<!-- Frase resumen para estudiante. Originalmente [Student Facing Goals] -->
<introduction component="est-goal"> 
  <p>Resolvamos problemas de sumas y restas.</p>
</introduction>

<!-- Objetivos para el estudiante. Originalmente [Student-Facing Targets] -->
<!-- <objectives component="estudiante">
  <ul>
    <li>[@@@@@@@@@@@@@@]</li>
  </ul>
</objectives> -->

<!-- Objetivos que solo ve el profesor. Originalmente [Teacher Facing Goals] -->
<objectives component="profesor">
  <ul>
    <li><p>[+++++++++++++++++]</p></li>
    <li>Solve addition and subtraction problems within 1,000 in a way that makes sense to them.</li>
  </ul>
</objectives>


<!-- ============================================ 
  Introducción para el profesor                        
=================================================  -->
<introduction component="profesor">

  <!-- Estándares CCSS asociados -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="ccss-leccion-titulo"/></title> 
    <ul>
      <li> 
        <custom ref="ccss-addressing"/>
        <xref ref="ccss-3-NBT-A-2" text="custom">3.NBT.A.2</xref>, 
        <xref ref="ccss-3-OA-D-9" text="custom">3.OA.D.9</xref>
      </li>      
    </ul>
    </paragraphs>

  <!-- índice de la lección (automático) -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="timeline-leccion-titulo"/></title>
    <list-of elements="subsubsection reading-questions" scope="subsection"/>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Propósito de la lección -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="purpose-leccion-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this lesson is for students to use addition and subtraction to solve problems within 1,000.</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Materiales requeridos -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="materials-leccion-titulo"/></title>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>Actividad 1</p>
        <xi:include href="./act-monumentosYCataratas-mat.ptx"/>
        <!--<xi:include href="./act-monumentosYCataratas-matCentros.ptx"/>-->
      </li>
      <!--<li>
        <p>Actividad 2</p>
        <xi:include href="./act-diarioSobreConexiones-mat.ptx"/>
        <xi:include href="./act-diarioSobreConexiones-matCentros.ptx"/>
      </li>-->
    </ul>  
  </paragraphs>
  
  <!-- Introducción de la lección (narrative) -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-leccion-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>Prior to this grade, students used various strategies and representations to solve problems involving addition and subtraction of multi-digit numbers (first within 100, and then within 1,000).</p>
    <p>This lesson enables the teacher to see the strategies and representations that students use, which may include base-ten blocks or diagrams, number lines, or equations. It also elicits what students know about using place value to add or subtract (for instance, combining hundreds and hundreds, tens and tens, and ones and ones). The work here prepares students to learn algorithms for addition and subtraction, which are also grounded in the same ideas.</p>
  </paragraphs>
  
  <!-- Preguntas de reflexión profesor -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="reflection-quest-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>What strategy did you anticipate today? Which did you not anticipate?</p>
  </paragraphs>
</introduction>


